1
00:00:01,543 --> 00:00:03,295
DOCTOR: Get down!

2
00:00:03,921 --> 00:00:06,757
-Ah! They're following us.
-And the good news is?

3
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:10,260
Their life spans are running out,
so we hide, wait for them to die.

4
00:00:10,344 --> 00:00:13,180
I have to stop being a Time Lord.
I'm going to become human.

5
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:15,432
Chameleon Arch. Rewrites my biology.

6
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,852
"A Journal of Impossible Things."

7
00:00:18,936 --> 00:00:21,355
-Such imagination!
-It's become quite a hobby.

8
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:23,774
He's different from any man
you've ever met, right?

9
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:24,942
Yes.

10
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:27,986
He had to go and fall in love
with a human. And it wasn't me.

11
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:30,197
If they find us, Martha, open the watch.

12
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:32,824
Sometimes I say things
and they turn out to be correct.

13
00:00:37,621 --> 00:00:39,206
They've found us.

14
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,584
-Oh, my God! Where's the watch?
-What are you talking about?

15
00:00:42,668 --> 00:00:45,963
This is not you. This is 1913.

16
00:00:46,046 --> 00:00:47,339
Change back!

17
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:52,302
We need a Time Lord.

18
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:55,889
Which one of them
do you want us to kill?

19
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:58,767
Doesn't this scare you enough
to change back?

20
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,979
Your friend or your lover?

21
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:06,525
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

22
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:46,064
JENNY: Make your decision, Mr Smith.

23
00:01:48,442 --> 00:01:52,696
BAINES: Perhaps if that human heart
breaks, the Time Lord will emerge.

24
00:01:53,572 --> 00:01:55,616
-Time Lord.
-Tim!

25
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:56,867
(SCREAMING)

26
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,285
All right!

27
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,704
One more move and I shoot.

28
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:04,249
-Oh, the maid is full of fire!
-And you can shut up!

29
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:07,169
Careful, Son of mine.

30
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:10,047
She's all for you
so that you can live forever.

31
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:11,548
Shoot you down.

32
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:13,925
Try it. We'll die together.

33
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:17,179
Would you really pull the trigger?

34
00:02:18,722 --> 00:02:20,599
Looks too scared.

35
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:22,517
Scared and holding a gun
is a good combination.

36
00:02:22,601 --> 00:02:24,603
Do you want to risk it?

37
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:35,072
Doctor, get everyone out.
There's a door at the side.

38
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,240
It's over there. Go on!

39
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:40,118
MARTHA: Do it, Mr Smith, I mean you!

40
00:02:40,202 --> 00:02:42,954
Do what she said. Everybody out now!

41
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:46,291
Don't argue, Mr Jackson.
They're mad, that's all we need to know.

42
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:48,335
Susan, Miss Cooper, outside, all of you!

43
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:54,091
Move yourself, boy.
Back to the school, quickly!

44
00:02:54,257 --> 00:02:56,802
-And you, go on, just shift.
-What about you?

45
00:02:56,885 --> 00:03:00,806
Mr Smith, I think you should escort
your lady friend to safety, don't you?

46
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:12,275
Mr Hicks, warn the village.
Get everyone out.

47
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:14,194
Latimer, get back to the school.
Tell the headmaster...

48
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,863
Don't touch me! You're as bad as them.

49
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:24,538
Don't try anything.
I'm warning you, or sonny boy gets it.

50
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:28,625
-She's almost brave, this one.
-I should have taken her form.

51
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:31,920
Much more fun, so much spirit.

52
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:36,007
-What happened to Jenny? Has she gone?
-She is consumed. Her body's mine.

53
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:37,426
You mean she's dead?

54
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:40,804
Yes, and she went
with precious little dignity.

55
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:42,472
All that screaming.

56
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,683
BAINES: Get the gun!

57
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,685
Good work, soldier.

58
00:03:47,811 --> 00:03:52,315
Don't just stand there, move!
God, you're rubbish as a human. Come on!

59
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,443
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

60
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:57,070
(WEAPON FIRING)

61
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:04,119
Run! Ah, this is super.
We've been in hiding for too long.

62
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:05,746
This is sport!

63
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:09,583
I can smell the schoolteacher.
He's gone back to his academy.

64
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:12,002
And what do we know about her?

65
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:16,965
This body has traces of memory.
Was once her friend.

66
00:04:17,048 --> 00:04:19,885
Martha would go walking to the west.

67
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:22,345
Husband of mine,
follow the maid's scent.

68
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:26,433
Go to the west.
Find out what she was keeping secret.

69
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:27,851
Soldiers!

70
00:04:30,729 --> 00:04:33,523
As for you, Mother of mine,

71
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:37,319
let's go to school.

72
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:53,293
-What are you doing?
-Maybe one man can't fight them,

73
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:55,170
but this school teaches us
to stand together.

74
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,881
Take arms! Take arms!

75
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,133
-Stop doing that!
-You want me to fight, don't you?

76
00:05:00,217 --> 00:05:03,386
-Take arms! Take arms!
-1 say, sir, what's the matter?

77
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,723
Enemy at the door, Hutchinson,
enemy at the door.

78
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:09,184
Take arms!

79
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:19,361
-They're sounding the alarms.
-I wouldn't be so pleased, Son of mine.

80
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,404
These bodies are silly and hot,
they can damage and die.

81
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:22,989
That's why we need the Time Lord.

82
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:26,743
Indeed, they will have guns.
Perhaps a little caution.

83
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:31,122
Sister of mine,
you're such a small little thing.

84
00:05:31,206 --> 00:05:33,583
Find a way in and spy on them.

85
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:43,009
-You can't do this, Doctor. Mr Smith!
-Maintain position over the stable yard.

86
00:05:43,093 --> 00:05:44,761
They're just boys,
you can't ask them to fight.

87
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:46,763
-They don't stand a chance!
-They are cadets, Miss Jones.

88
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:49,474
They are trained to defend the King
and all his citizens and properties.

89
00:05:49,558 --> 00:05:52,561
What in thunder's name is this?

90
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:56,189
Before I devise an excellent
and endless series of punishments

91
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:58,859
for each and every one of you,
could someone explain,

92
00:05:58,942 --> 00:06:01,820
very simply and immediately,
exactly what is going on?

93
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:04,281
Headmaster, I have to report,
the school is under attack.

94
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,199
Really? Is that so?

95
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:08,785
Perhaps you and I
should have a word in private.

96
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:10,996
No, I promise you, sir.
I was in the village with Matron.

97
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:14,291
It's Baines, sir, Jeremy Baines,
and Mr Clark from Oakham Farm.

98
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:15,709
They've gone mad, sir. They've got guns.

99
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:19,588
They've already murdered people
in the village. I saw it happen.

100
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:21,756
-Matron, is that so?
-I'm afraid it's true, sir.

101
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:25,427
-Murder? On our own soil?
- I saw it, yes.

102
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:28,889
Perhaps you did well then, Mr Smith.

103
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:30,974
And what makes you think
the danger is coming here?

104
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:35,145
-Well, sir, they said, um...
-Baines threatened Mr Smith, sir.

105
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:38,106
Said he'd follow him. We don't know why.

106
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:40,901
Very well.

107
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:43,862
You boys remain on guard,
Mr Snell, telephone for the police.

108
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:45,822
Mr Phillips, with me.
We shall investigate.

109
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:47,365
No! It's not safe out there.

110
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:49,993
Mr Smith, it seems your
favourite servant is giving me advice.

111
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:52,162
You will control her, sir.

112
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,666
Got to find that watch.

113
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:03,089
DOCTOR: Hold me, keep me safe.

114
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:06,134
Keep me dark, keep me closed.

115
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:09,220
The time is not right, not yet.

116
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:13,016
Not while the Family is abroad. Danger!

117
00:07:16,019 --> 00:07:18,313
So, Baines,

118
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:21,358
and one of the cleaning staff.
There's always a woman involved.

119
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,986
Am I to gather that some practical joke
has got out of hand?

120
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:28,031
Headmaster, sir. Good evening, sir.
Come to give me a caning, sir?

121
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:30,116
-Would you like that, sir?
-Keep a civil tongue, boy.

122
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:34,287
Now, come on, everyone. I suspect
alcohol has played its part in this.

123
00:07:34,371 --> 00:07:35,705
Let's all just calm down.

124
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,708
Who are these friends of yours, Baines,
in fancy dress?

125
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:43,129
Do you like them, Mr Phillips?
I made them myself.

126
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:46,841
I'm ever so good at science, sir. Look.

127
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,887
Molecular fringe animation,
fashioned in the shape of straw men.

128
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:53,431
My own private army, sir.
It's ever so good, sir.

129
00:07:53,515 --> 00:07:55,684
Baines, step apart from this company
and come inside with me.

130
00:07:55,767 --> 00:08:00,730
No, sir. You, sir,
you will send us Mr John Smith.

131
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:03,066
That's all we want, sir, Mr John Smith,

132
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,986
and whatever he's done with
his Time Lord consciousness.

133
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,863
Then we'd be very happy
to leave you alone.

134
00:08:08,947 --> 00:08:11,992
You speak with someone else's voice,
Baines. Who might that be?

135
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:14,285
We are the Family of Blood.

136
00:08:14,411 --> 00:08:18,540
-Mr Smith said there had been deaths.
-Yes, sir, and they were good, sir.

137
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,667
Well, I warn you, the school is armed.

138
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,545
All your little tin soldiers.

139
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:27,007
But tell me, sir,

140
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:30,010
-will they thank you?
-I don't understand.

141
00:08:30,093 --> 00:08:34,264
What do you know of history, sir?
What do you know of next year?

142
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:37,726
-You're not making sense, Baines.
-1914, sir.

143
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:42,063
Because the Family has travelled
far and wide looking for Mr Smith,

144
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:44,607
and, oh, the things we have seen.

145
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:48,153
War is coming.

146
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:51,990
In foreign fields,
war of the whole wide world

147
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:55,326
with all your boys
falling down in the mud.

148
00:08:55,410 --> 00:09:00,331
Do you think they will thank the man
who taught them it was glorious?

149
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:03,501
Don't you forget, boy,
I have been a soldier.

150
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:07,422
I was in South Africa.
I used my dead mates for sandbags.

151
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:09,758
I fought with the butt of my rifle
when the bullets ran out,

152
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:12,510
and I would go back there tomorrow
for King and country.

153
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:14,596
Etcetera, etcetera.

154
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:20,894
Run along, Headmaster.
Run back to school.

155
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:23,396
And send us Mr Smith!

156
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:25,648
(JENNY LAUGHING)

157
00:09:40,163 --> 00:09:43,333
Mr Phillips has been murdered.
Mr Smith, can you tell me why?

158
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,876
Honestly, sir, I have no idea.

159
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:48,088
And the telephone line has been
disconnected. We are on our own.

160
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:51,466
Well, if we have to make a fight of it,
then make a fight we shall.

161
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:54,928
Hutchinson, we'll build a barricade
within the courtyards.

162
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:57,597
Fortify the entrances,
build our defences.

163
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:02,143
Gentlemen, in the name of the King
we shall stand against them.

164
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:05,480
ALL: Yes, sir.
BOY: Right, come on. Let's get moving.

165
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:10,610
Down!

166
00:10:11,319 --> 00:10:14,864
Barricade the kitchens.
Secure the passageway to the stables.

167
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,866
You little coward.

168
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,119
You will do your duty, Latimer,
with the rest of us.

169
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:21,996
Sandbags to the north and west!

170
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:25,416
Williams, you take charge. Pemberton,
load the spare magazines with bullets.

171
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:27,460
SMITH: Take the magazine cut-off out.

172
00:10:28,378 --> 00:10:30,255
They've got an army.

173
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:33,133
So do we.

174
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:35,552
Soldiers.

175
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:37,595
Soldiers!

176
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:58,199
Ashington, we need water for
the Vickers gun. See to it.

177
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:00,451
Faster, all of you, faster.

178
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:07,834
Lockley, when firing commences,
you're in charge of the gathering.

179
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:11,588
Peterson, that's not acceptable.
Report to your senior officer.

180
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:30,648
War comes to England

181
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,902
a year in advance.

182
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:38,865
LUCY: Family of mine, wait.
Hold the soldiers back.

183
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:42,368
The Time Lord is playing
some sort of trick.

184
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:44,871
BAINES: Discover him, Sister of mine.

185
00:11:46,748 --> 00:11:49,876
I know it sounds mad,
but when the Doctor became human,

186
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:52,295
he took the alien part of himself
and he stored it inside the watch.

187
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,797
It's not really a watch,
it just looks like a watch.

188
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:59,344
And "alien" means not from abroad,
I take it?

189
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:03,973
The man you call John Smith,
he was born on another world.

190
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:06,309
-A different species.
-Yeah.

191
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,854
Then tell me, in this fairy tale,

192
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:12,649
who are you?

193
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:13,983
Just a friend.

194
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:18,279
I'm not... I mean, you haven't
got a rival, as much as I might...

195
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:21,157
-Just his friend.
-And human, I take it?

196
00:12:21,241 --> 00:12:24,118
Human, don't worry. More than that,
I don't just follow him around,

197
00:12:24,202 --> 00:12:25,912
I'm training to be a doctor.

198
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:28,665
Not an alien doctor,
a proper doctor, a doctor of medicine.

199
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:30,333
Well, that certainly is nonsense.

200
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:32,502
Women might train to be doctors,
but hardly the skivvy

201
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:35,004
and hardly one of your colour.

202
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:37,173
Oh, do you think?

203
00:12:39,384 --> 00:12:40,885
Bones of the hand.

204
00:12:40,969 --> 00:12:45,265
Carpal bones, proximal row:
scaphoid, lunate, triquetral, pisiform.

205
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:48,017
Distal row:
trapezium, trapezoid, cap it ate, ha mate.

206
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:51,062
Then the metacarpal bones
extending in three distinct phalanges:

207
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,064
proximal, middle, distal.

208
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:56,818
-Well, you read that in a book.
-Yes, to pass my exams!

209
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,947
-Can't you see this is true?
-I must go.

210
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:03,116
If we find that watch, we can stop them.

211
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,617
Those boys are going to fight.

212
00:13:04,701 --> 00:13:07,495
I might not be a doctor,
but I'm still their nurse.

213
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:09,414
They need me.

214
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:15,420
Son of mine, Wife of mine.

215
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,923
Father of mine, what have you found?

216
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:20,967
His Tardis.

217
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,052
The Doctor can't escape.

218
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:28,474
You're with Armitage and Thwaites,
they know the drill.

219
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:34,731
-Joan, it's not safe.
-I'm doing my duty, just as much as you.

220
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:39,944
Fine evening we've had together.

221
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:42,030
Not quite as planned.

222
00:13:43,406 --> 00:13:45,533
Tell me about Nottingham.

223
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:47,452
Sorry?

224
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:50,997
That's where you were brought up,
tell me about it.

225
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:56,711
Well, it lies on the River Leen

226
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:59,172
with its southern boundary
following the course of the River Trent,

227
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:01,758
which flows from Stoke to the Humber.

228
00:14:01,883 --> 00:14:04,927
That sounds like an encyclopaedia.
Where did you live?

229
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:06,262
Broadmarsh Street,

230
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,890
adjacent to Hockley Terrace
in the district of Radford Parade.

231
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:10,683
More than facts.

232
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:13,019
When you were a child,
where did you play?

233
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,937
All those secret little places,

234
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:18,232
the dens and hideaways
that only a child knows.

235
00:14:19,734 --> 00:14:22,320
Tell me, John, please, tell me.

236
00:14:22,445 --> 00:14:24,781
How can you think I'm not real?

237
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:29,786
-When I kissed you, was that a lie?
-No, it wasn't, no.

238
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:34,957
But this Doctor sounds like some...
Some romantic lost prince.

239
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:38,461
Would you rather that?

240
00:14:40,755 --> 00:14:43,925
-Am I not enough?
-No, that's not true, never.

241
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,551
I've got to go.

242
00:14:45,635 --> 00:14:48,888
Martha was right about one thing.
Those boys, they're children.

243
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:52,850
John Smith wouldn't want them to fight,
never mind the Doctor.

244
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:55,895
The John Smith I was getting to know,

245
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,064
he knows it's wrong.

246
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:01,109
-Doesn't he?
-Mr Smith, if you please!

247
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:04,821
What choice do I have?

248
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,960
Get those bags piled up, filth.

249
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:21,170
They're going to mean the difference
between life and death for us.

250
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:24,507
-Not for you and me.
-What are you babbling about?

251
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,342
We go to battle together.

252
00:15:28,386 --> 00:15:30,721
We fight alongside.

253
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:33,474
I've seen it. Not here, not now.

254
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:37,979
-What's that supposed to mean?
-It means you and I both survive this.

255
00:15:38,813 --> 00:15:40,565
And maybe...

256
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:44,193
Maybe I was given this watch
so I could help.

257
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,947
I'm sorry.

258
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:51,576
-Latimer, you filthy coward!
-Oh, yes, sir, every time.

259
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,046
What do I do?

260
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:07,967
What do I do? What do I do?

261
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,760
VOICES: Beware!

262
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:12,263
-Beware of what?
-VOICES: Her!

263
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:20,313
Keep away.

264
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:23,191
-Who are you?
-I saw you at the dance.

265
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:25,568
You were with that family,
you're one of them.

266
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:28,404
-What are you hiding?
-Nothing.

267
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,656
-What have you got there?
-Nothing.

268
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,658
Show me, little boy.

269
00:16:32,742 --> 00:16:36,913
I reckon, whatever you are,
you're still in the shape of a girl.

270
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:39,832
How strong is she, do you think?

271
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:42,418
Does she really want to see this?

272
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:49,509
-Time Lord!
-Inside the device.

273
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:53,596
Everything he is, concealed away
in the hands of a schoolboy.

274
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:56,641
But now we know
that's all we need to find,

275
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:59,352
the boy and the watch.

276
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:02,939
What are we waiting for? Attack!

277
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:10,780
(BANGING)

278
00:17:10,905 --> 00:17:12,365
Stand to!

279
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:15,243
(BANGING)

280
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:23,960
At post!

281
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,046
BOY: Enemy approaching, sir.

282
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:30,800
(BANGING)

283
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:32,969
Steady.

284
00:17:33,553 --> 00:17:35,680
Find the biting point.

285
00:17:37,682 --> 00:17:38,849
Fear...

286
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,363
Fire!

287
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,859
Cease fire!

288
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:43,372
Just straw.

289
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:47,627
Like he said. Straw!

290
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:50,796
Then no one is dead, sir.
We killed no one.

291
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,050
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

292
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:55,843
Stand to!

293
00:18:58,387 --> 00:19:01,098
You, child, come out of the way!
Come into the school!

294
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,642
You don't know who's out there.

295
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:05,311
It's the Cartwright girl, isn't it?
Come here, come to me.

296
00:19:05,394 --> 00:19:08,648
Mr Rocastle, please, don't go near her.

297
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:13,027
-You were told to be quiet.
-Just listen to me, she's part of it.

298
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:14,654
Matron, tell him.

299
00:19:14,737 --> 00:19:17,990
I think... I don't know, I think
you should stay back, Headmaster.

300
00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:22,578
-Mr Smith.
-She was with Baines in the village.

301
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:25,414
Mr Smith, I've seen
many strange sights this night,

302
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:28,334
but there is no cause on God's earth
that would allow me

303
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:31,629
to see this child
in the field of battle, sir.

304
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:34,256
-Come with me.
-You're funny.

305
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:37,176
That's right. Now, take my hand.

306
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:39,095
So funny.

307
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:48,521
Now, who's going to shoot me?
Any of you, really?

308
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:50,439
Put down your guns.

309
00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:52,525
But, sir, the Headmaster.

310
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:55,444
I'll not see this happen, not any more.

311
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:59,490
You will retreat in an orderly fashion
back through the school.

312
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:01,033
Hutchinson, lead the way.

313
00:20:01,117 --> 00:20:02,993
-But, sir...
-1 said, lead the way.

314
00:20:03,119 --> 00:20:05,788
Well, go on, then. Run!

315
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:07,998
-BAINES: Soldiers!
-Come on!

316
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:10,209
BAINES: Reanimate!

317
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,603
Let's go, quick as you can!

318
00:20:29,687 --> 00:20:31,313
Don't go to the village, it's not safe!

319
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:34,900
-And you, ladies.
-Not till we've got the boys out.

320
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:38,195
One of these boys has got the watch.

321
00:20:38,279 --> 00:20:40,448
-JENNY: This one?
-No.

322
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:42,324
-This one?
-No.

323
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:44,160
-JENNY: This one?
-No.

324
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:46,620
Get off me! I said get off!

325
00:20:46,704 --> 00:20:48,914
Ah! This one, is that him?

326
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:51,333
No.

327
00:20:51,459 --> 00:20:54,003
Right, then we can kill this lot.

328
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,506
MALE VOICE: Lord of time.

329
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:59,467
-That's him.
-Upstairs!

330
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:04,847
Well, don't just stand there, outside!
Come on, out!

331
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:14,857
I insist, the pair of you, just go!

332
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,277
If there are any more boys inside,
I'll find them.

333
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:20,738
I think... Retreat!

334
00:21:36,212 --> 00:21:38,923
CLARK: Doctor!

335
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:43,886
Doctor!

336
00:21:46,222 --> 00:21:49,725
Come back, Doctor. Come home!

337
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:52,603
Come and claim your prize.

338
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:56,065
Out you come, Doctor,
there's a good boy.

339
00:21:56,148 --> 00:21:58,317
Come to the Family.

340
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,653
Time to end it now!

341
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:02,238
MARTHA: You recognise it, don't you?

342
00:22:02,363 --> 00:22:04,824
JENNY: Come out, Doctor!

343
00:22:04,907 --> 00:22:06,367
Come to us.

344
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,369
I've never seen it in my life.

345
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:12,248
Do you remember its name?

346
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:16,919
I'm sorry, John, but you wrote about it.

347
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:20,923
The blue box, you dreamt of a blue box.

348
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:23,634
I'm not...

349
00:22:25,094 --> 00:22:27,680
I'm John Smith.
That's all I want to be, John Smith!

350
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:30,140
With his life and his job.

351
00:22:31,642 --> 00:22:34,687
And his love. Why can't I be John Smith?
Isn't he a good man?

352
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:37,481
-Yes, yes, he is.
-Why can't I stay?

353
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:41,068
But we need the Doctor.

354
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:46,949
And what am I, then? Nothing?

355
00:22:48,284 --> 00:22:49,994
I'm just a story.

356
00:22:56,292 --> 00:22:59,295
One more phase
and we won't have to hunt.

357
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:02,673
The Doctor, Mr Smith,
the boy, the watch,

358
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:05,217
they will come to us.

359
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:08,846
BAINES: Soldiers, guard this thing.

360
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:17,313
This way, I think I know
somewhere we can hide.

361
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,940
-We've got to keep going.
-Just listen to me for once, John.

362
00:23:20,024 --> 00:23:21,650
Now, follow me.

363
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:26,530
BAINES: Power up. Fully armed and ready.

364
00:23:27,031 --> 00:23:31,952
Mother, Father and Sister of mine,
prepare the armaments.

365
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:35,497
I doubt that England is ready for this.

366
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:38,250
Fix targets, and counting down.

367
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,591
Here we are. It should be empty.

368
00:23:46,342 --> 00:23:50,054
Oh, it's been a long time
since I've run that far.

369
00:23:50,179 --> 00:23:52,014
But who lives here?

370
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:54,224
If I'm right, no one.

371
00:24:06,362 --> 00:24:07,529
Hello?

372
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:12,701
No one home. We should be safe here.

373
00:24:12,785 --> 00:24:15,079
Whose house is it, though?

374
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,622
The Cartwrights'.

375
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:18,457
That little girl at the school,
she's Lucy Cartwright,

376
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:22,628
or she's taken Lucy Cartwright's form.
If she came home this afternoon,

377
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:26,298
and if the parents tried to stop
their little girl, then...

378
00:24:26,382 --> 00:24:28,217
they were vanished.

379
00:24:29,927 --> 00:24:31,845
Stone cold.

380
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:34,390
How easily I accept these ideas.

381
00:24:42,064 --> 00:24:44,608
I must go to them
before anyone else dies.

382
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:46,068
You can't.

383
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:49,446
Martha, there must be something
we can do.

384
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:50,823
Not without the watch.

385
00:24:50,906 --> 00:24:54,118
You're this Doctor's companion,
can't you help?

386
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:58,414
What exactly do you do for him?
Why does he need you?

387
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:00,916
Because he's lonely.

388
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:04,962
And that's what you want me to become?

389
00:25:07,256 --> 00:25:08,966
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

390
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:11,093
What if it's them?

391
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:16,932
I'm not an expert,
but I don't think scarecrows knock.

392
00:25:26,984 --> 00:25:28,819
I brought you this.

393
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:33,449
MARTHA: Hold it.

394
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:36,368
-I won't.
-Please, just hold it.

395
00:25:36,452 --> 00:25:38,996
It told me to find you.
It wants to be held.

396
00:25:39,121 --> 00:25:43,125
You've had this watch all this time?
Why didn't you return it?

397
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:45,627
Because it was waiting.

398
00:25:46,670 --> 00:25:50,257
Then because I was so scared
of the Doctor.

399
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:51,800
Why?

400
00:25:52,801 --> 00:25:54,136
Because

401
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:56,472
I've seen him.

402
00:25:57,890 --> 00:26:01,810
He's like fire and ice and rage.

403
00:26:02,978 --> 00:26:06,190
He's like the night and the storm
and the heart of the sun.

404
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:08,275
-Stop it.
-He's ancient and forever.

405
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:11,111
He burns at the centre of time,
and he can see the turn of the universe.

406
00:26:11,195 --> 00:26:13,113
Stop it! I said stop it.

407
00:26:13,197 --> 00:26:15,449
And he's wonderful.

408
00:26:22,539 --> 00:26:25,084
I've still got this, the journal.

409
00:26:25,709 --> 00:26:27,711
Those are just stories.

410
00:26:28,003 --> 00:26:30,923
Now we know that's not true.
Perhaps there's something in here...

411
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:32,174
(EXPLOSION)

412
00:26:32,257 --> 00:26:33,884
What the hell?

413
00:26:37,888 --> 00:26:40,182
This will flush him out,
this will do it!

414
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:41,850
Super, super fun!

415
00:26:44,478 --> 00:26:46,688
JOAN: They're destroying the village.

416
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:48,190
The watch!

417
00:26:49,358 --> 00:26:51,318
John, don't.

418
00:26:51,401 --> 00:26:52,694
DOCTOR: Closer.

419
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:55,948
-Can you hear it?
-Like he's asleep.

420
00:26:56,031 --> 00:26:58,826
-Waiting to waken.
-Why did he speak to me?

421
00:26:58,909 --> 00:27:00,953
Oh, low level telepathic field,
you were born with it.

422
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:03,914
Just an extra synaptic engram,
causing...

423
00:27:06,542 --> 00:27:09,169
-Is that how he talks?
-That's him!

424
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:11,713
All you have to do is open it,
and he's back.

425
00:27:11,839 --> 00:27:13,382
(EXPLOSION)

426
00:27:14,258 --> 00:27:17,094
You knew this all along and yet
you watched while Miss Redfern and I...

427
00:27:17,177 --> 00:27:19,429
I didn't know how to stop you.

428
00:27:19,513 --> 00:27:23,475
He gave me a list of things to
watch out for, but that wasn't included.

429
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:26,353
Falling in love?
That didn't even occur to him?

430
00:27:26,436 --> 00:27:29,231
-No.
-Then what sort of man is that?

431
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,234
And now you expect me to die?

432
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:35,737
It was always going to end, though.

433
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:37,865
The Doctor said the Family has got
a limited life span,

434
00:27:37,948 --> 00:27:40,409
that's why they need to consume
a Time Lord.

435
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:43,203
Otherwise, three months and they die.

436
00:27:43,579 --> 00:27:45,539
Like mayflies, he said.

437
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:49,209
So your job was to execute me?

438
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:52,963
People are dying out there.

439
00:27:53,714 --> 00:27:56,091
They need him, and I need him.

440
00:27:56,175 --> 00:27:58,051
'Cause you've got no idea
what he's like.

441
00:27:58,135 --> 00:28:02,055
I've only just met him,
it wasn't even that long ago, but...

442
00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:04,975
He is everything.

443
00:28:05,392 --> 00:28:08,145
He's just everything to me,
and he doesn't even look at me,

444
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:09,938
but I don't care.

445
00:28:10,939 --> 00:28:13,025
'Cause I love him to bits.

446
00:28:13,192 --> 00:28:16,069
And I hope to God
he won't remember me saying this.

447
00:28:19,114 --> 00:28:20,949
It's getting closer.

448
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:24,286
I should have thought of it before.
I can give them this!

449
00:28:24,411 --> 00:28:25,996
Just the watch.

450
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:27,748
Then they can leave
and I can stay as I am.

451
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,041
You can't do that!

452
00:28:29,124 --> 00:28:30,626
If they want the Doctor,
they can have him.

453
00:28:30,751 --> 00:28:33,629
-He'll never let you do it.
-And if they get what they want, then...

454
00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:36,131
Then it all ends in destruction.

455
00:28:36,798 --> 00:28:38,592
I never read to the end.

456
00:28:38,675 --> 00:28:43,138
Those creatures will live forever,
to breed and conquer.

457
00:28:43,222 --> 00:28:46,350
A war across the stars, for every child.

458
00:28:48,185 --> 00:28:53,232
Martha, Timothy,
would you leave us alone, please?

459
00:28:56,485 --> 00:28:58,445
(SOBBING)

460
00:29:27,391 --> 00:29:30,727
If I could do this instead of you,
then I would.

461
00:29:35,232 --> 00:29:36,733
I'd hoped...

462
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:40,779
But my hopes aren't important.

463
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:43,031
He won't love you.

464
00:29:43,699 --> 00:29:46,660
If he's not you,
then I don't want him to.

465
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:51,540
I had one husband and he died and I...

466
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:54,042
I never thought, ever again...

467
00:29:56,169 --> 00:29:57,671
And then you.

468
00:29:59,172 --> 00:30:02,384
-You're so...
-And it was real, I wasn't...

469
00:30:04,344 --> 00:30:06,096
I really thought...

470
00:30:08,598 --> 00:30:10,058
Let me see.

471
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,352
Blasted thing.

472
00:30:13,312 --> 00:30:15,022
Blasted, blasted thing.

473
00:30:15,105 --> 00:30:18,150
I can't even hear it,
it says nothing to me.

474
00:30:24,239 --> 00:30:26,074
(BABY CRYING)

475
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:33,790
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

476
00:30:41,131 --> 00:30:43,383
They're all safe, aren't they?

477
00:30:43,467 --> 00:30:45,594
The children,

478
00:30:46,345 --> 00:30:48,096
the grandchildren.

479
00:30:49,639 --> 00:30:51,350
Everyone's safe.

480
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:54,770
Everyone's safe.

481
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:58,982
-And they all send their love, John.
-Well, then.

482
00:31:00,734 --> 00:31:02,069
It's time.

483
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:04,613
Thank you.

484
00:31:11,036 --> 00:31:12,496
Did you see?

485
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:16,541
The Time Lord has such adventures.

486
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:22,422
But he could never
have a life like that.

487
00:31:22,631 --> 00:31:24,299
And yet I could.

488
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,766
What are you going to do?

489
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:42,109
We'll blast them into dust,
then fuse the dust into glass

490
00:31:42,192 --> 00:31:44,694
then shatter them all over again!

491
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:47,364
Just...

492
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,827
Just stop the bombardment.

493
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:54,788
That's all I'm asking.
I'll do anything you want, just stop.

494
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:56,540
Say please.

495
00:31:58,125 --> 00:31:59,418
Please.

496
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:03,130
(CONTROLS DEACTIVATING)

497
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,173
Wait a minute.

498
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,761
Still human.

499
00:32:09,845 --> 00:32:12,431
Look, I can't pretend to understand,
not for a second,

500
00:32:12,514 --> 00:32:15,308
but I want you to know,
I'm innocent in all this.

501
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:20,105
He made me John Smith.
It's not like I had any control over it.

502
00:32:20,188 --> 00:32:24,693
He didn't just make himself human,
he made himself an idiot.

503
00:32:25,152 --> 00:32:27,112
Same thing, isn't it?

504
00:32:27,195 --> 00:32:29,531
I don't care about this Doctor
and your family,

505
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:31,533
I just want you to go!

506
00:32:32,451 --> 00:32:34,536
So I've made my choice.

507
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:37,038
You can have him.

508
00:32:38,206 --> 00:32:40,125
Just take it, please, take him away!

509
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:41,585
At last!

510
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:50,927
Don't think that's saved your life!

511
00:32:52,888 --> 00:32:54,598
Family of mine,

512
00:32:56,808 --> 00:32:59,811
now we shall have the lives
of a Time Lord.

513
00:33:05,275 --> 00:33:06,943
It's empty!

514
00:33:09,905 --> 00:33:12,240
-Where's it gone?
-You tell me!

515
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:16,369
Oh, I think the explanation might be
you've been fooled

516
00:33:16,453 --> 00:33:18,830
by a simple olfactory misdirection.

517
00:33:18,914 --> 00:33:21,708
A little bit like
ventriloquism of the nose.

518
00:33:21,791 --> 00:33:23,793
It's an elementary trick
in certain parts of the galaxy.

519
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:25,629
But it has got to be said,

520
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:28,423
I don't like the look
of that hydrokinometer.

521
00:33:28,507 --> 00:33:30,926
It seems to be indicating
you've got energy feedback

522
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:32,677
all the way through
the retrostabilisers,

523
00:33:32,761 --> 00:33:35,764
feeding back into
the primary heat converters.

524
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:37,307
Oh!

525
00:33:37,390 --> 00:33:40,185
'Cause if there's one thing
you shouldn't have done,

526
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:42,854
you shouldn't have let me press
all those buttons.

527
00:33:42,938 --> 00:33:46,483
But, in fairness,
I will give you one word of advice.

528
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:48,777
Run.

529
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:50,111
(ALARM SOUNDING)

530
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:52,781
Get out! Get out!

531
00:34:22,644 --> 00:34:26,731
BAINES: He never raised his voice,
that was the worst thing.

532
00:34:26,815 --> 00:34:29,401
The fury of the Time Lord.

533
00:34:29,484 --> 00:34:31,236
And then we discovered why,

534
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:34,489
why this Doctor, who had fought
with gods and demons,

535
00:34:34,573 --> 00:34:37,576
why he'd run away from us and hidden.

536
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,452
He was being kind.

537
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:45,959
He wrapped my father
in unbreakable chains

538
00:34:46,042 --> 00:34:48,670
forged in the heart of a dwarf star.

539
00:34:50,547 --> 00:34:52,924
He tricked my mother
into the event horizon

540
00:34:53,008 --> 00:34:56,261
of a collapsing galaxy,
to be imprisoned there

541
00:34:57,596 --> 00:34:58,847
forever.

542
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:06,771
He still visits my sister,
once a year, every year.

543
00:35:07,981 --> 00:35:10,233
I wonder if one day
he might forgive her,

544
00:35:10,317 --> 00:35:12,152
but there she is, can you see?

545
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:15,322
He trapped her inside a mirror.

546
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:18,617
Every mirror.
If ever you look at your reflection

547
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:23,455
and see something move behind you,
Just for a second, that's her.

548
00:35:23,538 --> 00:35:25,540
That's always her.

549
00:35:27,459 --> 00:35:31,212
As for me, I was suspended in time,

550
00:35:31,296 --> 00:35:36,134
and the Doctor put me to work
standing over the fields of England

551
00:35:36,217 --> 00:35:38,011
as their protector.

552
00:35:41,348 --> 00:35:43,558
We wanted to live forever.

553
00:35:44,601 --> 00:35:47,228
So the Doctor made sure that we did.

554
00:36:10,251 --> 00:36:11,711
Is it done?

555
00:36:12,921 --> 00:36:14,297
It's done.

556
00:36:15,632 --> 00:36:18,176
The police and the army are at school.

557
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:20,220
Parents have come to take the boys home.

558
00:36:20,303 --> 00:36:23,306
I should go.
They'll have so many questions.

559
00:36:23,848 --> 00:36:25,975
I'm not sure what to say.

560
00:36:29,354 --> 00:36:30,563
Oh.

561
00:36:31,981 --> 00:36:33,775
You look the same.

562
00:36:34,401 --> 00:36:37,278
Goodness,
you must forgive my rudeness. I...

563
00:36:38,947 --> 00:36:41,116
I find it difficult to look at you.

564
00:36:41,241 --> 00:36:43,952
Doctor, must call you Doctor.

565
00:36:45,453 --> 00:36:46,955
Where is he?

566
00:36:48,373 --> 00:36:51,084
-John Smith.
-He's in here, somewhere.

567
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,586
Like a story.

568
00:36:54,337 --> 00:36:56,881
-Could you change back?
-Yes.

569
00:36:58,133 --> 00:37:00,218
-Will you?
-No.

570
00:37:03,263 --> 00:37:04,806
I see.

571
00:37:06,599 --> 00:37:07,976
Well, then.

572
00:37:11,312 --> 00:37:13,940
He was braver than you, in the end.

573
00:37:15,233 --> 00:37:17,360
That ordinary man.

574
00:37:19,195 --> 00:37:21,114
You chose to change,

575
00:37:22,115 --> 00:37:23,867
he chose to die.

576
00:37:26,244 --> 00:37:28,288
-Come with me.
-Sorry?

577
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:30,373
Travel with me.

578
00:37:31,458 --> 00:37:33,334
-As what?
-My companion.

579
00:37:34,210 --> 00:37:36,171
But that's not fair.

580
00:37:37,672 --> 00:37:40,508
What must I look like to you, Doctor?

581
00:37:41,676 --> 00:37:44,471
-I must seem so very small.
-No.

582
00:37:45,388 --> 00:37:48,016
We could start again. I'd like that.

583
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:50,977
You and me, we could try, at least.

584
00:37:52,353 --> 00:37:55,398
'Cause everything
that John Smith is and was,

585
00:37:56,441 --> 00:37:58,651
I'm capable of that, too.

586
00:37:59,736 --> 00:38:02,322
-I can't.
-Please come with me.

587
00:38:02,405 --> 00:38:04,532
-I can't.
-Why not?

588
00:38:06,993 --> 00:38:09,954
John Smith is dead,
and you look like him.

589
00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:15,210
But he's here.

590
00:38:16,377 --> 00:38:17,712
Inside.

591
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:21,966
If you look in my eyes...

592
00:38:23,885 --> 00:38:27,138
Answer me this,
just one question, that's all.

593
00:38:28,723 --> 00:38:31,267
If the Doctor had never visited us,

594
00:38:32,060 --> 00:38:35,438
never chosen this place on a whim,

595
00:38:37,649 --> 00:38:40,360
would anyone here have died?

596
00:38:47,826 --> 00:38:49,619
You can go.

597
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:38,793
Right, then, motto bene.

598
00:39:40,461 --> 00:39:42,380
How was she?

599
00:39:42,463 --> 00:39:44,132
Time we moved on.

600
00:39:44,215 --> 00:39:47,635
-If you want, I could go and...
-Time we moved on.

601
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:52,390
Erm, meant to say,
back there last night,

602
00:39:52,515 --> 00:39:54,225
I would've said anything
to get you to change.

603
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:56,352
-Oh, yeah, course you would.
-I wasn't really...

604
00:39:56,436 --> 00:39:57,604
-No, no, no.
-Good.

605
00:39:57,687 --> 00:39:59,272
-Fine.
-So there we are, then.

606
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:01,441
There we are, then, yes.

607
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:04,360
And I never said.

608
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,614
Thanks for looking after me.

609
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:15,455
Doctor, Martha.

610
00:40:16,164 --> 00:40:18,124
Tim Timothy Tim!

611
00:40:18,207 --> 00:40:20,501
I just wanted to say goodbye,

612
00:40:21,294 --> 00:40:22,837
and thank you.

613
00:40:22,962 --> 00:40:27,050
Because I've seen the future,
and I now know what must be done.

614
00:40:27,634 --> 00:40:31,179
It's coming, isn't it?
The biggest war ever.

615
00:40:31,304 --> 00:40:34,182
-You don't have to fight.
-I think we do.

616
00:40:34,682 --> 00:40:36,351
But you could get hurt.

617
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:38,227
So could you,
travelling around with him,

618
00:40:38,311 --> 00:40:40,521
but it's not going to stop you.

619
00:40:40,605 --> 00:40:43,858
Tim, I'd be honoured if you'd take this.

620
00:40:49,238 --> 00:40:51,074
I can't hear anything.

621
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:55,912
No, it's just a watch now.
But keep it with you for good luck.

622
00:40:57,205 --> 00:40:59,082
Look after yourself.

623
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:09,592
You'll like this bit.

624
00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:15,431
(WHOOSHING)

625
00:41:31,614 --> 00:41:33,324
SOLDIER: Incoming!

626
00:41:34,283 --> 00:41:36,661
DOCTOR: In June, 1914,

627
00:41:36,786 --> 00:41:40,581
an archduke of Austria
was shot by a Serbian.

628
00:41:40,665 --> 00:41:44,544
And this then lead, through nations
having treaties with nations,

629
00:41:44,627 --> 00:41:47,463
like a line of dominoes falling,

630
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:53,094
to some boys from England walking
together in France on a terrible day.

631
00:41:53,845 --> 00:41:55,930
One minute past the hour.

632
00:41:56,806 --> 00:41:58,474
It's now.

633
00:41:58,599 --> 00:42:00,977
Hutchinson, this is the time, it's now.

634
00:42:01,102 --> 00:42:02,520
(SHELL WHISTLING)

635
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,605
To the right, to the right!

636
00:42:14,657 --> 00:42:16,451
We made it.

637
00:42:19,579 --> 00:42:21,330
Thank you, Doctor.

638
00:42:23,374 --> 00:42:25,126
Come on, old chap.

639
00:42:26,169 --> 00:42:29,672
-Leave me. I'm not going to make it.
-Oh, yes you are.

640
00:42:29,756 --> 00:42:31,340
Didn't I promise you
all those years ago?

641
00:42:31,424 --> 00:42:33,968
Now, come on, and that's an order!

642
00:42:56,991 --> 00:43:00,244
...they went with songs to the battle.
They were young,

643
00:43:00,328 --> 00:43:05,249
straight of limb, true of eye,
steady and aglow.

644
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:09,295
They were staunch to the end
against odds uncounted.

645
00:43:09,378 --> 00:43:12,298
They fell with their faces to the foe.

646
00:43:13,966 --> 00:43:18,346
They shall not grow old
as we that are left grow old.

647
00:43:19,806 --> 00:43:24,060
Age shall not weary them
nor the years condemn.

648
00:43:25,061 --> 00:43:28,689
At the going down of the sun
and in the morning,

649
00:43:29,357 --> 00:43:31,609
we will remember them.

650
00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:41,410
Don't blink.

651
00:43:41,494 --> 00:43:43,454
Blink and you're dead.

652
00:43:43,830 --> 00:43:45,706
Don't turn your back,

653
00:43:45,790 --> 00:43:49,001
don't look away and don't blink.

654
00:43:51,754 --> 00:43:53,172
Good luck.

